S l^-7/2 -9/2 S l^-5/2. Thus the abutment becomes an important analytical\nand numerical laboratory for studying the evolution of Q and i in Kerr\nspacetime and for testing current and future radiation back-reaction models for\nnear-polar retrograde orbits.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Jul 2010 19:20:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 29 Sep 2010 18:46:37 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 20 Nov 2010 22:29:29 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 19 Jan 2011 18:50:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-01-20"}
