exity that only depends on the proximity\nparameter $\\e$.\n  Our algorithm for finding cycles in bounded-degree graphs extends to general\ngraphs, where distances are measured with respect to the actual number of\nedges. Such an extension is not possible with respect to finding tree-minors in\n$o(\\sqrt{N})$ complexity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 23 Jul 2010 23:34:05 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 27 Jul 2010 00:56:59 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 3 Apr 2012 17:37:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-04-04"}
